text: The lovely leaf frog (Phyllomedusa venusta) is a frog that lives in Venezuela, Colombia, and Panama. Scientists have seen it between 800 and 1400 meters above sea level. This frog lives in trees and peoplehave seen it on plants in forest with water in the air. It has been found in places that human beings have changed. This frog lays eggs in swamps and ponds. This frog is not in danger of dying out because it lives in such a large place. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Phyllomedusa venusta
